Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_gui_edit_callback(25.10)                report_gui_edit_callback(25.10)

Name
       report_gui_edit_callback  - Reports the callback functions added to the
       specified move action

Syntax
       report_gui_edit_callback

       [-help]

       [-edit_type {selection pre-move post-move}]

       [-file <string>]

       Reports the callback functions added to the specified move  action.  In
       GUI, the move action involves the following three steps:

              * Click an object.

              * Move the object to the new location.

              * Click to place the object at the new location and complete the
                move.

       The callback function is implemented based on the move action specified
       with the -edit_type parameter.

       Note  that the report_gui_edit_callback command does not report the de-
       fault callback functions.

Parameters
       -help  Prints the usage of the command. For a detailed  description  of
              the command, use the man command:

              man report_gui_edit_callback

       -edit_type {selection pre-move post-move}
              Specifies the GUI edit function:

              * selection - Implements the callback function when an object is
                selected (after Step 1).

              * pre-move  -  Implements  the callback function just before the
                object is placed at the new location (after Step 2,  just  be-
                fore you change the coordinates in Step 3).

              * post-move  -  Implements the callback function after an object
                is moved (after Step 3, when the tool updates the DB records).

       -file <string>
              Specifies the name of the file.

Example
       Consider the following proc definitions:

       proc move_callback_1 {

            ...

       }

       proc move_callback_2 {

            ...

       }

       proc select_callback_1 {

            ...

       }

              * The following commands add the specified callback functions to
                the selected object based on the selection and  on  the  post-
                move operations, as specified below:

       register_gui_edit_callback  -edit_type  post-move  -command  move_call-
       back_1

       register_gui_edit_callback  -edit_type  post-move  -command  move_call-
       back_2

       register_gui_edit_callback  -edit_type  selection -command select_call-
       back_1

              * The following command reports all the  callback  functions  on
                the console:

       > report_gui_edit_callback

       ################################

       # GUI Callback Function Report

       ################################

       Post Move:

       move_callback_1

       move_callback_2

       Selection:

       select_callback_1

              * The  following  command  prints  the callback functions on the
                post-move operation to the file cb_move:

                report_gui_edit_callback -edit_type post-move -file cb_moveThe
                contents of the file is as follows:

